article.headline: Oral Roberts 69, S. Utah 61
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Ken Tutt scored 21 points and went 8-for-8 from the foul line in the final minute in Oral Roberts' 69-61 win over Southern Utah on Thursday night. Caleb Green scored all of his 17 points in the second half for the Golden Eagles (10-7, 3-0 Mid-Continent), while Marchello Vealy had 11 rebounds. Steve Barnes led the Thunderbirds (10-7, 0-2) with 18 points. Justin Allen added 10 in Southern Utah's first home loss of the season. Oral Roberts outrebounded Southern Utah 39-28 and went 23-for-30 from the foul line. After Tate Sorensen gave Southern Utah its last lead on a layup with 19:14 left, the Eagles went on a 12-1 run that featured two turnaround jumpers by Green and a 3-pointer by Adam Liberty. The Thunderbirds went nearly seven minutes without a field goal before Swaney Cooper scored on a reverse layup with 12:24 remaining. Southern Utah got within 46-43 and held Oral Roberts to only four field goals in the last 12 minutes, but the Eagles sealed it from the line.
